BLUG will be doing an eclectic December festivey event loosely themed around open processes in often-closed fields: we have talks from Columb Duffy of Allstate on how they have begun to implement InnerSource at ANI (open source processes in international companies), Mal Duffin on doing 3D game development with open source Blender, and me (Phil Weir) talking about taking open data from government departments to make an open education tool
Non-alcoholic & vegetarian available. Newcomers & curious welcome to all events.
